                                    <dt>Schedule 2 (Items 1-7) – Tax Relief Availment:</dt>
                                    <dd>Taxpayer availing of any tax relief under the Tax Code must completely fill-up Items 1-7.</dd>

                                    <p>For ECOZONES: Gross income shall refer to gross sales or gross revenue derived from registered business activity within the zone, net of sales discounts, sales returns and allowances minus cost of sales or direct costs but before any deductions for administrative, marketing, selling, operating expenses or incidental losses during a given taxable period.</p>
                                    <p>For BCDA: Gross income shall refer to gross sales or gross revenue derived from registered business activity within the zone, net of sales discounts, sales returns and allowances minus cost of sales or direct costs but before any deductions for administrative, marketing, selling, operating expenses or incidental losses during a given taxable period. For financial enterprises, gross income shall include interest income, gains from sales and other income net of costs of funds.</p>


